        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 6:41PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 28 miles north of Ryegate to 19 miles
south of Ryegate, or extending from 31 miles northwest of Roundup to
27 miles north of Columbus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roundup, Ryegate, Broadview, Lavina, Klein, Comanche, Acton and
Hailstone Wildlife Refuge. This does not include Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
